author: Patti Domm
title: Jobless claims expected to spike to a record-breaking number in the millions
description: About 1 million to 4 million people are expected to have filed for unemployment last week, the largest number ever. The data is released Thursday.
content:
Job seekers stand in line at the employment help center in Miami, Florida.
About 1 million to 4 million people may have filed for unemployment benefits last week, the largest number ever in such a short time.
